00:14:33,122 --> 00:14:38,544
♪ <i>I said, ooh, I'm blinded by the lights </i> ♪

229
00:14:39,086 --> 00:14:43,132
♪ <i>No, I can't sleep</i>
<i>Until I feel your touch </i> ♪

230
00:14:43,215 --> 00:14:45,175
♪ <i>Hey! Hey! Hey! Hey! </i> ♪

231
00:14:54,268 --> 00:14:56,770
- Get the bird! Get the bird!
- I got the bird.

232
00:14:56,854 --> 00:14:58,272
Did you see…

233
00:15:02,359 --> 00:15:06,238
Sorry! On vocal rest, can't talk.
On vocal rest.

234
00:15:06,322 --> 00:15:08,490
- Scooter, what is going on here?
- Hmm?

235
00:15:08,574 --> 00:15:10,159
Am I on next or what?

236
00:15:10,242 --> 00:15:14,288
Oh, uh. Kermit had to cut your number,
Miss Piggy. Didn't he tell you?

237
00:15:14,371 --> 00:15:16,999
What? Does it look like he told me?

238
00:15:17,082 --> 00:15:21,420
You think I'm wearing these gladiator
sandals for my freaking health?

239
00:15:21,503 --> 00:15:23,130
Uh… Probably not.

240
00:15:23,213 --> 00:15:27,509
- Kermit!
- Whoa!

241
00:15:28,510 --> 00:15:30,763
Yep. Good to be back.

242
00:15:32,139 --> 00:15:33,974
So sorry about the mishap earlier.

243
00:15:34,058 --> 00:15:35,935
We're still working out a few kinks.

244
00:15:36,018 --> 00:15:38,312
Oh, that's all right. I love a kink.

245
00:15:38,395 --> 00:15:40,439
Uh-huh. Hmm.

246
00:15:40,522 --> 00:15:42,316
Well, uh, I just wanted to say

247
00:15:42,399 --> 00:15:44,818
we're really honored
to have you here with us tonight.

248
00:15:44,902 --> 00:15:45,903
Are you kidding me?

249
00:15:45,986 --> 00:15:47,738
- Being here is a dream come true.
- Ah.

250
00:15:47,821 --> 00:15:49,925
I mean, I could've been
anywhere else in the world tonight.

251
00:15:49,949 --> 00:15:51,992
- I… I turned down a Pulitzer prize…
- Mmm. Mmm.

252
00:15:52,076 --> 00:15:56,038
…and getting my face on the new quarter,
and a second date with…

253
00:15:56,956 --> 00:15:58,415
- Really?
- Mm-hmm.

254
00:15:59,124 --> 00:16:00,542
- He's single?
- No.

255
00:16:00,626 --> 00:16:01,794
Oh.

256
00:16:01,877 --> 00:16:03,963
But this is the only place
I want to be right now.

257
00:16:04,046 --> 00:16:05,589
And nothing could...

258
00:16:06,173 --> 00:16:07,853
Open the door, frog!

259
00:16:07,883 --> 00:16:09,194
- Sorr…
- She knows, boss!

260
00:16:09,218 --> 00:16:10,362
I think someone's at the door.

261
00:16:12,388 --> 00:16:14,682
Uh, ooh, that?

262
00:16:14,765 --> 00:16:17,726
No, no, no, no. That's, uh…
That's just an old theater, you know?

263
00:16:17,810 --> 00:16:20,729
- Uh, these pipes can be pretty noisy.
- Hi-yah!

264
00:16:22,564 --> 00:16:23,565
Where is he?

265
00:16:24,066 --> 00:16:26,110
Wow, the door wasn't even locked.

266
00:16:26,193 --> 00:16:28,570
I know you're here, frog.

267
00:16:28,654 --> 00:16:29,923
Miss Piggy?

268
00:16:29,947 --> 00:16:32,908
I'm sure you get this all the time,
I actually meant to tell you earlier,

269
00:16:32,992 --> 00:16:34,493
but you're my idol.

270
00:16:34,576 --> 00:16:36,120
- Aw.
- Yeah,

271
00:16:36,203 --> 00:16:39,456
I basically, like, modeled my whole look
and style after you.

272
00:16:39,540 --> 00:16:43,961
Oh, trust me. My attorneys and I have
taken notice, and we will be in touch.

273
00:16:44,044 --> 00:16:48,841
Aw. And I'll make sure
my attorneys respond… to your attorneys.

274
00:16:50,426 --> 00:16:51,635
Did you hear that?

275
00:16:51,719 --> 00:16:55,556
Oh, Kermit said the theater is really old
and the pipes are a little noisy.

276
00:16:55,639 --> 00:16:58,517
Oh, really? What else did Kermit say?

277
00:16:58,600 --> 00:17:00,978
Did he mention he cut my big number
from the show?

278
00:17:01,061 --> 00:17:03,063
What? No. That-That's crazy.

279
00:17:03,147 --> 00:17:05,232
There's no <i>Muppet Show</i>
without a Miss Piggy number.

280
00:17:05,315 --> 00:17:06,650
Exactly.

281
00:17:06,734 --> 00:17:08,360
If only he were around to hear that.

282
00:17:08,444 --> 00:17:10,237
Door's heavy.

283
00:17:10,320 --> 00:17:11,697
I am so sorry.

284
00:17:11,780 --> 00:17:15,117
You don't deserve to lose one second
of screen time. You are an icon.

285
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:18,662
Oh, stop it. You're too sweet. Go on.

286
00:17:18,746 --> 00:17:23,125
Oh, I mean, I grew up watching you,
my parents grew up watching you,

287
00:17:23,208 --> 00:17:26,336
- their parents grew up watching…
- Okay! Meet-and-greet over.

288
00:17:26,420 --> 00:17:28,231
If Kermit ever shows his face,

289
00:17:28,255 --> 00:17:32,342
you let him know.
I am going to sing in this show!

290
00:17:33,218 --> 00:17:36,722
- Help me.
- Oh, no! That's right.

291
00:17:36,805 --> 00:17:38,849
Are you okay? Sorry.

292
00:17:38,932 --> 00:17:40,076
I forgot you were down there.

293
00:17:40,100 --> 00:17:42,478
Hey, I'm fine, Sabrina. Yeah, I…

294
00:17:42,561 --> 00:17:44,039
It happens a lot more than you'd think.

295
00:17:44,063 --> 00:17:45,689
Uh, Scooter!

296
00:17:45,773 --> 00:17:48,400
You know the drill.
Let's get another door in here.

297
00:17:48,484 --> 00:17:49,610
Already on it, boss.

298
00:17:51,695 --> 00:17:54,156
I've actually met Kermit a few times.

299
00:17:54,239 --> 00:17:55,741
He's actually really lovely.

300
00:17:56,241 --> 00:17:58,452
I mean, I've met a ton of celebrities.

301
00:17:58,535 --> 00:17:59,745
A lot of jerks.

302
00:17:59,828 --> 00:18:02,164
But not Kermit.

303
00:18:02,664 --> 00:18:06,627
- Was I a big jerk?
- I mean, yes. But not that big.

304
00:18:06,710 --> 00:18:08,504
Mmm?

305
00:18:08,587 --> 00:18:09,797
- Oh, I'm Maya by the way.
- Mmm?

306
00:18:15,761 --> 00:18:16,762
Mm-hmm.

307
00:18:24,770 --> 00:18:27,981
Welcome to Muppet Labs,
where the future is being made today.

308
00:18:28,065 --> 00:18:32,820
I'm Dr. Bunsen Honeydew,
and this is my fearless assistant Beaker.

309
00:18:36,365 --> 00:18:37,908
Hmm.

310
00:18:37,991 --> 00:18:41,245
Today we tackle
a modern epidemic: Distraction.

311
00:18:41,328 --> 00:18:42,621
These days,

312
00:18:42,704 --> 00:18:45,207
everything is competing for your eyeballs.

313
00:18:45,290 --> 00:18:48,544
Mobile devices, televisions
and the day-to-day terrors

314
00:18:48,627 --> 00:18:52,297
that consume our brains
when we aren't looking at the first two.

315
00:18:52,381 --> 00:18:55,175
Well, now you can focus effortlessly

316
00:18:55,259 --> 00:18:58,679
thanks to my latest invention,
"Focus Pocus."

317
00:18:58,762 --> 00:19:01,473
One drop of this serum per eye,

318
00:19:01,557 --> 00:19:04,434
and your attention span
will multiply exponentially.

319
00:19:06,061 --> 00:19:08,772
Beaker, come back,
come back. Sit on the stool.

320
00:19:09,314 --> 00:19:11,150
- Huh?
- That's it. Good. Now,

321
00:19:11,233 --> 00:19:13,318
I'm gonna just lower the stool gently.

322
00:19:13,944 --> 00:19:16,071
There, there we go.

323
00:19:16,155 --> 00:19:18,323
A little teeny drop.
This won't hurt me at all.

324
00:19:19,616 --> 00:19:21,869
There we go. There, there, there.

325
00:19:23,787 --> 00:19:27,499
Oh, dear. That might've been
just a teensy bit too strong.

326
00:19:32,254 --> 00:19:34,590
Hmm.

327
00:19:34,673 --> 00:19:36,800
Maybe I neglected to dilute it properly.

328
00:19:36,884 --> 00:19:38,486
Now, let's see.
Where did I write that down?

329
00:19:43,390 --> 00:19:45,767
Oh, this is interesting.

330
00:19:45,851 --> 00:19:47,644
This one's marked urgent.

331
00:19:47,728 --> 00:19:48,979
Hmm. I'm sure that's fine.

332
00:19:53,609 --> 00:19:57,237
Oh, Beaker. Beaker.
Beaker, stop it. Stop it!

333
00:19:58,071 --> 00:20:00,324
- It's so inspiring.
- Inspiring.

334
00:20:00,407 --> 00:20:02,951
- I feel alive, you know?
- Mm-hmm.

335
00:20:03,035 --> 00:20:04,912
I mean, as a performer…

336
00:20:06,663 --> 00:20:09,833
Maya? Maya? M-Maya!

337
00:20:09,917 --> 00:20:11,376
Scooter,

338
00:20:11,460 --> 00:20:13,420
my mommy's in the audience tonight.

339
00:20:13,503 --> 00:20:15,505
When do I go on? Scooter! Scooter!

340
00:20:15,589 --> 00:20:18,800
I will be ready as soon as I do my…

341
00:20:18,884 --> 00:20:22,471
Oh, wow. Like, are you okay, Kermit?

342
00:20:22,554 --> 00:20:23,931
Yeah.

343
00:20:24,014 --> 00:20:25,891
'Cause you seem a little wound up.

344
00:20:25,974 --> 00:20:29,394
Like, like your chakras are,
like, totally out of whack.

345
00:20:29,478 --> 00:20:32,481
You're right.
I guess I am a little stressed.

346
00:20:32,564 --> 00:20:34,191
Thanks for checking in.

347
00:20:34,274 --> 00:20:40,322
Oh, for sure. 'Cause you know, like,
I can read auras, and yours is, like, bad.

348
00:20:42,074 --> 00:20:43,992
- It is?
- Oh, totally.

349
00:20:44,076 --> 00:20:46,245
And we're breathing in…

350
00:20:46,328 --> 00:20:49,831
- Oh, is that what we're doing?
- Uh…

351
00:20:52,542 --> 00:20:55,212
Janice? Can I breathe out yet?

352
00:20:55,796 --> 00:20:58,632
Hmm? Janice?

353
00:20:59,549 --> 00:21:03,387
Oh. Huh. Actually,
that did make me feel a bit better.

354
00:21:03,470 --> 00:21:05,597
Almost like
things are gonna be okay.

355
00:21:06,390 --> 00:21:08,475
This is a <i>Muppet Newsflash</i>.

356
00:21:08,558 --> 00:21:11,937
Emmy award-winning comedy icon
Maya Rudolph is dead.

357
00:21:14,439 --> 00:21:15,440
Huh?

358
00:21:16,108 --> 00:21:19,611
I saw the light,
and there was a river of souls.

359
00:21:19,695 --> 00:21:22,030
And a… a wall of flames.

360
00:21:22,114 --> 00:21:24,658
And I was doing award show patter
for a man in red.

361
00:21:26,451 --> 00:21:29,913
That sounds like heaven. Right?

362
00:21:29,997 --> 00:21:34,251
Correction. Emmy award-winning comedy icon
Maya Rudolph is alive.

363
00:21:34,334 --> 00:21:37,546
A thing fell on her
and made her be alive again.

364
00:21:37,629 --> 00:21:40,007
Stay tuned for more hard-hitting news.

365
00:21:40,090 --> 00:21:43,218
…Whoopi Goldberg, Anjelica Huston,
Cloris Leachman.

366
00:21:43,302 --> 00:21:45,846
Hmm. Show's not half bad.

367
00:21:45,929 --> 00:21:47,597
Yeah, it's all bad.

