♪ <i>To another world</i> ♪

402
00:24:05,444 --> 00:24:10,198
- ♪ <i>And we rely on each other, ah ha</i> ♪
- ♪ <i>Ah ha</i> ♪

403
00:24:10,282 --> 00:24:16,580
- ♪ <i>From one diva to another, ah ha</i> ♪
- ♪ <i>Ah ha</i> ♪

404
00:24:23,587 --> 00:24:25,422
Oh.

405
00:24:25,505 --> 00:24:26,506
- Hi.
- Hmm?

406
00:24:26,590 --> 00:24:28,800
I just have to say singing a duet with you

407
00:24:28,884 --> 00:24:30,969
- has always been a dream of mine.
- Mmm.

408
00:24:31,052 --> 00:24:33,388
And now I've done it,
and I'm still so young.

409
00:24:33,972 --> 00:24:37,893
Yes! Just like me! I'm young. Very.

410
00:24:37,976 --> 00:24:41,646
Look at us, two young ingenues
at the top of their game.

411
00:24:48,820 --> 00:24:51,531
Well, um… Does this mean we're…
we're good then?

412
00:24:51,615 --> 00:24:54,075
You're not gonna try to sue me
for stealing your look?

413
00:24:54,159 --> 00:24:56,411
It's called copyright infringement,
sweetie.

414
00:24:56,495 --> 00:24:58,997
- And of course not!
- Oh.

415
00:24:59,956 --> 00:25:01,875
That's really for the lawyers to decide.

416
00:25:04,336 --> 00:25:06,087
I'm trying to do the best I can.

417
00:25:07,047 --> 00:25:09,424
…one of the acts. We're trying to be fair.

418
00:25:09,925 --> 00:25:12,302
- We're trying to be fair to everybody.
- I know. No, I know.

419
00:25:12,385 --> 00:25:14,304
Okay, everybody, stop!

420
00:25:14,387 --> 00:25:18,767
There is only time
for one more act.

421
00:25:18,850 --> 00:25:20,644
- What?
- One more?

422
00:25:20,727 --> 00:25:22,312
- But which one, boss?
- Hmm?

423
00:25:22,395 --> 00:25:24,314
How are you gonna choose?

424
00:25:24,397 --> 00:25:26,650
What's taking them so long?

425
00:25:33,532 --> 00:25:36,451
Look, do you trust me?

426
00:25:36,535 --> 00:25:41,915
Well, of course we do, Kermit.
I mean, maybe not this guy.

427
00:25:43,542 --> 00:25:44,876
I been burned before.

428
00:25:46,920 --> 00:25:50,131
Okay, uh…
Give me a minute, okay?

429
00:25:50,215 --> 00:25:52,318
- Where you going? Wait…
- Yeah. Excuse me. I'm sorry.

430
00:25:52,342 --> 00:25:54,761
- What… What's he gonna do?
- Kermit?

431
00:25:58,640 --> 00:26:02,477
Hey there, folks.
Uh, how you all doing so far?

432
00:26:03,436 --> 00:26:05,105
Ooh. Um…

433
00:26:05,188 --> 00:26:09,276
I can't say that the show
has gone exactly the way we planned.

434
00:26:09,359 --> 00:26:13,363
Jamie Lee Curtis. Regina King!

435
00:26:13,947 --> 00:26:18,076
Eh, the point is…
…maybe we're a little rusty.

436
00:26:18,159 --> 00:26:21,788
But, uh, but we promised
to do a great show for you

437
00:26:21,871 --> 00:26:26,126
and, uh… …I hope that you
at least enjoyed some of it.

438
00:26:31,464 --> 00:26:33,133
Now we're at the end

439
00:26:33,216 --> 00:26:37,262
and you're all probably wondering
what the final number is.

440
00:26:37,345 --> 00:26:39,764
I-In fact, I was supposed to come out here

441
00:26:39,848 --> 00:26:42,642
and announce one of the acts
waiting backstage.

442
00:26:43,810 --> 00:26:50,025
But, um… …I'm sorry.
Uh, I'm not gonna do that.

443
00:26:52,652 --> 00:26:54,946
See? Can't trust anyone.

444
00:26:55,530 --> 00:26:56,656
Mmm.

445
00:26:59,993 --> 00:27:02,287
♪ <i>Tonight</i> ♪

446
00:27:02,370 --> 00:27:08,251
♪ <i>We're gonna have ourselves</i>
<i>A real good time</i> ♪

447
00:27:08,335 --> 00:27:14,215
♪ <i>I feel alive</i> ♪

448
00:27:16,217 --> 00:27:21,723
♪ <i>And the world</i>
<i>I'll turn it inside out</i> ♪

449
00:27:21,806 --> 00:27:23,099
Yeah.

